Those ‘lucky’ enough to pass the interviews can become heads of departments or even principals without portfolio.The teachers are like crabs in a bucket; one tries climbing up and reaches the edge just about to jump out, another climbs onto his back and they all fall back into the turmoil below If one needs to study the workplaces where there is a concentration of people with degrees, one need not look further. Just visit the nearest high school. Everyone you say ‘hallo’ to must be having several degrees and diplomas.
In such a situation, it is not easy to talk of meaningful career progression. The moment one gets employed and is posted to a school, he immediately realises the futility of even attempting to jump the ladder and grow. You find people that have stagnated in the same job group long before you were born.



