Qualified locals
Picture that the qualified locals are heading fast to their retirement and may even retire before the incumbent. The recipe is complete and something grand must happen to make way.
There are the times you will hear of an improbable rape case in a well-secured school, with students complaining about almost everything, and sexual harassment may be rumoured to be smothered by the principal.
This may seem far-fetched and ghastly, but they happen frequently and the public always supports the removal ‘lax’ headteachers.
Some resign while those that swear their innocence find themselves thrown as far away as possible. What goes to the bin is forgotten.
The teachers are like crabs in a bucket; one tries climbing up and reaches the edge just about to jump out, another climbs onto his back and they all fall back into the turmoil below.
It is in this context that we wish you to view the case of supposed rape in a big school in western Kenya. Find out what really happened after the investigations are completed.
